# The Moment of Truth

An FTP test protocol. Your FTP is 95% of your average power during the 20-minute effort. Pace yourself — go too hard early and you'll blow up. Go too easy and you're leaving watts on the table.

- 10:00 45%
  - :30 Welcome to the FTP test
  - 3:00 We'll warm up for 10 minutes at an easy pace
  - 3:00 Keep your cadence smooth and steady
  - 2:00 Openers coming up — three short efforts to prime the legs
- 1:00 100%
  - :05 Opener 1 — get the legs firing
- 1:00 40%
- 1:00 100%
  - :05 Opener 2 — shake out the cobwebs
- 1:00 40%
- 1:00 100%
  - :05 Opener 3 — one more
- 1:00 40%
- 5:00 45%
  - :30 Easy spinning — save everything for the test
  - 3:00 The 20-minute test starts in 2 minutes
  - 1:00 Find your gear — you want to start controlled
- 5:00 95%
  - :10 Ramp into it — don't explode out of the gate
  - 2:00 Find your rhythm, this isn't the test yet
  - 2:00 Settle in, the real effort starts next
- 20:00 100%
  - :10 HERE WE GO — 20 minutes, give it everything
  - 5:00 5 minutes in — check your power, is this sustainable?
  - 5:00 Halfway — stay focused, don't look at the clock
  - 3:00 7 minutes to go — now it hurts, that's normal
  - 2:00 5 minutes left — don't you dare back off
  - 2:00 3 minutes — you can do anything for 3 minutes
  - 1:00 2 minutes — start emptying the tank
  - 1:00 FINAL MINUTE — everything you have left, leave it all here
- 10:00 40%
  - :10 That's it! You did it. Spin easy
  - 3:00 Great effort — remember, FTP is 95% of that average
  - 5:00 Keep spinning to flush out the legs
